filename: mutant clap noise output cutoff sweep.wav_424639.wav
tags: modular, eurorack, drum, clap
description: This is part of a set of samples demonstrating the capabilities of the DIY version of the Hexinverter Mutant Clap module (eurorack/modular synth). Of particular note is the noise bleed present in some Hexinverter DIY products as discussed on the muffwiggler forum. Except where noted as "WITH VCA," all samples are recorded without added effects or processing. "WITH VCA" samples have been tidied up with an envelope modulated VCA. One may choose to see the bleed as a feature or flaw...

tags: tom-tom, 96-24, MIDI, 96-KHz, percussion, tom, drum, GM
description:
This is a small, 10" tom with Remo Ambassador and Pinstripe drumheads. It is tuned to E3. Batter skin is Pinstripe.

Recorded with AKG D-40 and Rode NT5-MP microphones. There's analogue compression and digital post-processing.

Samples are mixed with close to -0 dB peaks, there're 6 velocity zones, -6 is the highest (127-106 MIDI velocity suggested, 22/21-unit divisions) and -1 is the lowest (0-22).

tags: Stereo, Bass, Instrument, Double, Plucked, Standup, Upright, Acoustic
description: This standup bass was sampled using a direct pickup as well as stereo overhead mics for some room ambience.  Articulations include a normal pizzicato, or finger plucked note; a stopped note as performed with the finger; a stopped note performed Bartok style; and some miscellaneous sound effects: a slide by the hand down the strings, a slap on the strings, and a knock on the wooden body of the bass.  Do enjoy; feedback is welcome!
